-# Top-of-form error summary banner. Render at the top of a form
-# inside a model-bound block — checks `model.errors` and renders a
-# soft-danger card listing every error (field-level messages stay
-# inline next to their input via the _field partial, so the banner
-# acts as the "what's wrong" overview rather than the only place
-# errors surface).
-#
-# Locals:
-#   model       — the AR model (or any object that responds to
-#                 :errors with full_messages support)
-#   resource    — optional human-readable noun ("user", "computer";
-#                 default derived from the model's class.name)

- return unless model && model.respond_to?(:errors) && model.errors.any?
- count = model.errors.count
- resource ||= model.class.model_name.human.downcase

.rounded-md.border.border-danger-soft.bg-danger-soft.p-3.text-danger-soft-text{ role: "alert", "aria-live": "polite" }
  %div.flex.items-start.gap-2
    = mesa_icon(:warn, size: 14, css: "mt-0.5 shrink-0")
    %div.min-w-0
      %p.font-semibold{ class: "text-[13px]" }
        = pluralize(count, "error")
        prevented this
        = resource
        from being saved.
      %ul.mt-1.list-disc.pl-5.space-y-0.5{ class: "text-[12px]" }
        - model.errors.full_messages.each do |message|
          %li= message
